
[1]animadvert

   ANIMADVERT', v.i. [L. animadverto, of animus, mind, and adverto, to
   turn to.]

   1. To turn the mind to; to consider.

   2. To consider or remark upon by way of criticism or censure.

   3. To inflict punishment; followed by upon.
